{"key":"processedPost-9286430","value":{"id":9286430,"first":9285885,"last":9289649,"when":1227309168,"utime":"11/22/08 01:12 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />and after two days I start shaking the jars once every day and every things fine tell the fifth day or so. <br /></blockquote><br /><br />That's where you're going wrong.&nbsp; You're assaulting your mycelium, weakening it.&nbsp; Shake grains only once, at about 20% to 40% colonization.&nbsp; You won't shake again until the day you shake to loosen the grains to use them as spawn.<br /><br />Oat berries work fine for spawn.&nbsp; If they're easier to get than rye, use them.&nbsp; However, don't shake every day because it damages and weakens the mycelium, allowing competitors to take over.<br />RR","title":"Re: Rye Grain Blues","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}